            "title": "The usefulness of thruth : an enquiriy concerning economic modelling",
            "abstract": "Philosophy of Science, Philosophy of Economics, Methodology, Empiricism, Pragmatism, Postmodernism, Anything goes, Relativism, Normativity. - This thesis attempts to justify a normative role for methodology by sketching a pragmatic way out of the dichotomy between two major strands in economic methodology: empiricism and postmodernism. I discuss several methodological approaches and assess their aptness for theory appraisal in economics. I begin with the most common views on methodology (i.e. empiricism and postmodernism) and argue why they are each ill-suited for giving methodological prescriptions to economics. Then, I consider positions that avoid the errors of empiricism and postmodernism. I specifically examine why the two major strands of methodological criticism fail to give helpful methodological advice to economists and sketch out a pragmatic approach that can do this.",
